</picture></div><p>A step-by-step guide on how to write a business letter.</p></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=prepare-your-document-before-writing>Prepare your document before writing.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=format-the-letter>Format the letter.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-formatting-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Format the letter."></div></div><p>The most common layout for a business letter is known as <strong>block format</strong>, where the entire letter is <strong>left-justified</strong> and <strong>single-spaced</strong>, with a <strong>double space between paragraphs</strong>. Business letters typically have <strong>1-inch (25.4 mm) margins</strong> on all sides of the page.</p><p>The generally accepted font is <strong>Times New Roman, 12 pt.</strong>, although other fonts like Arial are sometimes used.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consider the style of the company you are addressing when choosing a font.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-the-appropriate-paper-to-print-on>Choose the appropriate paper to print on.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-paper-288x288-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose the appropriate paper to print on."></div></div><p>A business letter should be printed on "letter size" paper, which is 8.5" by 11" in size. Outside the U.S., you can use paper size A4. For a lengthier contract, you can use 8.5" by 14" paper, otherwise known as "legal size."</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Print your business letter on your company's letterhead. This will provide a more professional appearance as well as providing your company's contact information.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=begin-crafting-your-business-letter>Begin crafting your business letter.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=type-out-your-company-information>Type out your company information.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-company-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Type out your company information."></div></div><p>This goes in the top left-hand corner of your page, with each part of the address written on a new line. You should not include your (or the sender's) name or title as you will list that information in the closing.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you are sending your letter to an international company, be sure to type out your country in capital letters.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=type-the-date>Type the date.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-date-288x288-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Type the date."></div></div><p>Leaving an open space after your company information, type out the date in full for a more professional look. If you took a couple of days to write your letter, use the date on which you finished. When writing to a recipient within the U.S., use the American date format: month, day, year.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=add-the-recipient-039-s-information>Add the recipient&#039;s information.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-recipient-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Add the recipient&#039;s information."></div></div><p>Leave a line open after the date and add your recipient's full name, title (if applicable), company name, and address. Type out international recipients' countries in capital letters on the last line. Each piece of information should appear, in this order, on a separate line. You may also include a reference number, if necessary.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Address your letters to a specific person. If you don't know their name, do some research or call the company.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-an-appropriate-salutation>Choose an appropriate salutation.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-salutation-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose an appropriate salutation."></div></div><p>Finally, and after leaving another line open after your recipient's information, <a
href="#types-of-salutations">choose an appropriate salutation</a> depending on the person you are writing to, how well you know them, and how formal your relationship is.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section2-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-the-introduction>Write the introduction.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-introduction-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write the introduction."></div></div><p>Start your letter with a <a
href="#different-ways-to-start-a-business-letter">short introductory paragraph</a>. It should include a friendly but professional opening and the main point(s) of the letter.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=compose-the-body-of-the-letter>Compose the body of the letter.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-the-letter>Write the letter.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-bodytext-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write the letter."></div></div><p>In a formal yet friendly tone write the body of your letter. The first paragraph can include a friendly opening but should focus on a statement of the main point. The second paragraph should justify the importance of the main point. Each subsequent paragraph should continue the justification with background information and supporting details. The closing paragraph should restate your main point and request action.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Keep it to one page if possible.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Refer to yourself as "I" and your reader as "you" to keep your letter concise and to the point. If you are writing on your company or organization's behalf, use "we" so that the reader knows your company is behind you.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Your last paragraph should summarize your points, your planned course of action, and what you expect from the recipient.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=close-the-letter>Close the letter.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-the-ending>Write the ending.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-signature-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write the ending."></div></div><p><a
href="#types-of-closing">Choose an appropriate closing</a> that is an indicator of respect and formality, and use a comma after your closing. Always use a positive closing, with only the first letter capitalized. Sign the letter.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Blue or black ink is the most common, and preferred, choice for signing a business document.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=add-your-information>Add your information.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-sendinfo-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Add your information."></div></div><p>After the signature block, type in your name, title, phone number, email address, and any other appropriate means of communication. Each piece of information should be in its own line. Do not include your company's address as it is at the top of the page.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>If you did not type the letter, the typist's initials should be added next in lower case.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-any-enclosures>Include any enclosures.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-enclosures-288x288-20200813.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include any enclosures."></div></div><p>For any additional documents added to your letter, note the number and type of documents beneath your contact information. For example, "<a
href="#different-ways-to-end-a-business-letter">Enclosures</a> (2): brochure, market analysis." This ensures the reader does not miss any important information.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>If you are sending the letter to another person, you should include this information. Type "cc:" below the enclosures with the person's name and title.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>If you are sending the letter to more than one person, align the second name under the first, but without the "cc".</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=edit>Edit.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-write-a-business-letter-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=carefully-edit-your-letter>Carefully edit your letter.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-write-a-business-letter-edit-288x288-2020089.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Carefully edit your letter."></div></div><p>Be sure to check spelling, punctuation, grammar, and professional appearance. You can run spell check but also read through your letter as spell check does not catch all nuances.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
